<item>
            <title>[CXF-5528] CXF Blueprint resource classes should have a more simple definition</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-5528</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When defining serviceBeans in the blueprint xml file, we first have to define the bean then reference that bean from the serviceBean definition.  It would be nice to have a short cut that allowed us to just define the class name in the rsServer xml.  Something like &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &amp;lt;jaxrs:server id=&quot;karafStringService&quot; address=&quot;/karaf&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;jaxrs:resourceClasses&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;class name=&quot;com.example.test.cxf.StringRestServiceImpl&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/jaxrs:resourceClasses&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/jaxrs:server&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will be submitting a patch shortly with an associated test.  I look forward to feedback.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
